# Intuition
Definitely we need to check each and every possible string.
> String length is 20, then we should not worry about time limit. 
> Even if length is greater, time will be still constant *(better explained in `Complexity Section`)*

We have three conditions:
```
1. Number of dots should be exactly 3.
2. When we take 2 or 3 letters make sure first letter shouldn't be zero.
3. We can only take any number from 0-255.  
```

# Approach
1. Take initial string `temp` as empty and  a variable for `dot` count.
2. Take all possibilities.
```
Possibility 1: Take 1 number.
Possibility 2: Take 2 number but also check that first letter shouldn't be '0'.
Possibility 3: Take 3 number but also check that first letter shouldn't be '0'and number shouldn't exceed 255.
```
3. When complete string traversed and `dots are 3` then insert it in `unordered_set`.
> In code, insert element when dots are 4 because we delete last dot as well before inserting.
4. `If dots exceeds 4 return`.
5. Copy all elements from `set to vector` and then `return vector`

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
> The IP address ranges from 0.0.0.0 to 255.255.255.255
So, there can be maximum 2^32 address 
Time complexity will be `constant` ---- **O(2^32)**  ----> **`O(1)`**.
- Space complexity:
> **`O(N) + Auxiliary space`**
Using a unordered_set and recursion stack

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    unordered_set<string> set;
    void sol(int i, string s, string temp,int dot)
    {
        if(i>=s.size())
        {
            if(dot==4)
            {
                temp.pop_back();
                set.insert(temp);
            }
            return;
        }
        if(dot>=4) return;
        sol(i+1,s,temp+s.substr(i,1)+'.',dot+1);
        if(s[i] != '0') sol(i+2,s,temp+s.substr(i,2)+'.',dot+1);
        if(s[i] !='0' && stoi(s.substr(i,3))<=255)
            sol(i+3,s,temp+s.substr(i,3)+'.',dot+1);

    }
    vector<string> restoreIpAddresses(string s) {
        sol(0,s,"",0);
        vector<string> ans(set.begin(),set.end());
        return ans;
    }
};
```

