# Intuition 
Iterative Approach 
# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1. If the length of the given string is greater than 12 that means there is no valid ip as maximum number is 255 and it has only 3 charater and we have to divide the string and insert dot 4 times.
2. Now divide the string into substrings and verify the condition on each substring
 - length is less then or equal to 3 
 - no leading zeros and
 - it's value in integer is less than or equal to 255
3. At the end insert the string into ans vector. 
# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(1)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(1)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Please Upvote if it helps you.

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    bool check(string str){
        if (str.size() == 1)
        return true;
        if (str.size() > 3|| str[0] == '0'|| stoi(str) > 255)
        return false;
        else
        return true;
    }
    vector<string> restoreIpAddresses(string s) {
        // check for length of the string as 255 has length 3 and only 4 such number are allowed
        if (s.size() > 12)
        return {};
        vector<string> v;
        for (int i = 1; i <= 3 ; i++)
        for (int j = 1 ; j <= 3 ; j++)
        for (int k = 1 ; k <= 3 ; k++)
        {
            if (i+j+k <s.size() && i+j+k+3 >= s.size()){
                string a =s.substr(0,i);
                string b =s.substr(i,j);
                string c =s.substr(i+j,k);
                string d =s.substr(i+j+k);
                if (check(a) && check(b) && check(c) && check(d))
                v.push_back(a+"."+b+"."+c+"."+d);
            }
        }
        return v;
    }
};
```

